- [ ] Explain what a token is used for.

Many services out in the wild require the client (our React app, for example) to provide proof that it’s authenticated
with them. The server running these services can issue a JWT (JSON Web Token) as the authentication token, in exchange for correct login credentials.

- [ ] What steps can you take in your web apps to keep your data secure?

Use HTTPS, SSL certificate, secures transfer of sensitive info. 
Installing security programs, will prevent hacking attempts. 
Keep website platform and software up to date, will prevent security vulnerabilities. 

- [ ] Describe how web servers work.

Either a computer stores the code for a website or a program runs on such a computer.

- [ ] Which HTTP methods can be mapped to the CRUD acronym that we use when interfacing with APIs/Servers.

PUT is the “U” in CRUD and it stands for UPDATE We use the PUT method to change a resource’s information. 
The DELETE HTTP request method is also the “D” in CRUD. We use this to Delete or destroy data that lives elsewhere.
